<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<knowl mode="exercise" xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.2">
    <intro>
        <p>
In each of the following, the given information 
determines a line in the plane.
        </p>
        <list>
            <item><p>Write an equation of the line, and</p></item>
            <item><p>sketch a graph of the line including the given point(s).</p></item>
        </list>
    </intro>
    
    <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>
The line with slope <m>{{slope}}</m> and through the point <m>{{point}}</m>. 
            </p>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <list>
                <item><p>The equation for the line</p>
                    <list>
                    <item><p>in slope-intercept form: <m>y = {{sl_int_ans1}}</m></p></item>
                    <item><p>in point-slope form (<em>PREFERRED</em>):
                        <m>y = {{pty}} {{ans_sign1}} {{slope}} \left( {{deltax}} \right)</m></p></item>
                    </list>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <p>The graph of the line:</p>
                    <p><image
                            source="assets/PBL1/generated/{{__seed__}}/Show1.png"
                            description="a red line with given slope through given blue point"
                        />
                    </p>
                    <p>Check the scale on the <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> 
                    axes to verify the slope is correct.
                    </p>
                </item>
            </list>
        </outtro>
    </knowl>

    <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>
The line through the points <m>({{x0}},{{y0}})</m> and <m>({{x1}},{{y1}})</m>.
            </p>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <list>
                <item><p>The equation for the line</p>
                    <list>
                    <item><p>in slope-intercept form: <m>y = {{sl_int_ans2}}</m></p></item>
                    <item><p>in point-slope form (<em>PREFERRED</em>):</p>
                        <p><m>y = {{y0}} {{ans_sign2}} {{m}} \left( {{deltax0}} \right)</m>, or</p>
                        <p><m>y = {{y1}} {{ans_sign2}} {{m}} \left( {{deltax1}} \right)</m></p></item>
                    </list>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <p>The graph of the line:</p>
                    <p><image
                            source="assets/PBL1/generated/{{__seed__}}/Show2.png"
                            description="a red line through the two given blue points"
                        />
                    </p>
                    <p>Check the scale on the <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> 
                    axes to verify the slope is correct.
                    </p>
                </item>
            </list>
        </outtro>
    </knowl>
</knowl>